{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13627,"record_hash":"sha256:80d86ec308140eabadf3fa9398abe86151604b1a44270dd885c451f90a406569","timestamp":"2026-05-09T16:44:20.008Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Everything is stored under this local-only prefix:\n\n```text\nmeta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:<agent>:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nFor example:\n\n```text\nmeta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:codex:sha256-abcd...:transcript\n```\n\n`<session-key>` is a hashed key derived from the transcript session id when present, otherwise from the canonical transcript path.\n\n**Scalar Keys**\nThe writer stores these scalar values in GitMeta from [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:156):\n\n```text\n:provider           if known, raw string\n:model              if known, raw string\n:cwd                if known, raw string\n:tool-version       if known, raw string\n:session-id         if known, stores the hashed session_key, not the raw session id\n:source-path        canonical transcript path, raw/local\n:source-size        full transcript snapshot byte length\n:source-sha256      sha256:<hex> of the full transcript snapshot\n:last-record-index  highest parsed source record index, or -1\n:captured-at        UTC timestamp for this capture\n```\n\nIt also stores:\n\n```text\n:seen-record-hashes\n```\n\nas a GitMeta set. Each value is the `sha256:<hex>` hash of one trimmed JSONL record.\n\n**Transcript List**\nThe big one is:\n\n```text\n:transcript\n```\n\nThis is a GitMeta list. Each list entry is a JSON string shaped like [TranscriptEnvelope](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:78):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n  \"agent\": \"codex\",\n  \"provider\": \"openai\",\n  \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\",\n  \"session_id\": \"session-1\",\n  \"source_record_index\": 0,\n  \"source_record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"source_timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T09:00:00Z\",\n  \"source_event_kind\": \"session_meta\",\n  \"turn_id\": null,\n  \"message_id\": null,\n  \"parent_message_id\": null,\n  \"role\": null,\n  \"cwd\": \"/path/to/repo\",\n  \"git_branch\": null,\n  \"source_record_redacted\": false,\n  \"source_record_redactions\": 0,\n  \"source_record\": {\n    \"...\": \"the parsed original provider JSON record, with string values redacted when needed\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nOne subtle but important detail: the original raw JSONL line is not stored verbatim. The code stores the parsed `serde_json::Value` as `source_record`, after redaction. The raw trimmed line is only represented by its `source_record_hash`.\n\nDedup is split in two places: `seen-record-hashes` tracks metadata-side capture, while the transcript list is deduped by reading existing envelope `source_record_hash` values before appending.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T16:44:20.008Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}